{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017724,"pPcc":"SAT#S","questionId":"aef4fd8a","skill_cd":"S.A.","score_band_range_cd":4,"skill_desc":"Area and volume","createDate":1755117017724,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Geometry and Trigonometry","ibn":"","external_id":"d1c64540-1ef9-4449-9ccf-d158b23af654","primary_class_cd":"S","uId":"ac336dcc-143d-449f-8dfc-0f7c64467811","difficulty":"M"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The length of each side of a square is <math alttext=\"94\"><mn>94</mn></math> centimeters (cm). Which expression gives the area, in <math alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the square?</p>","keys":["313f2015-afa0-4676-a9e6-a2ba0780b135"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"9eba2c8a-bad2-4708-9289-4dca6ce91a32","content":"<p><math alttext=\"2 dot 94\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math></p>"},{"id":"5cbdc099-5b25-4e18-bc15-a6b807a4a6ba","content":"<p><math alttext=\"2 dot 94 dot 94\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math></p>"},{"id":"d7028cb1-8905-46d5-aa1c-8f6e9b889b1c","content":"<p><math alttext=\"4 dot 94\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math></p>"},{"id":"313f2015-afa0-4676-a9e6-a2ba0780b135","content":"<p><math alttext=\"94 dot 94\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math></p>"}],"rationale":"<p>Choice D is correct. The area of a square is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s squared\"><msup><mi>s</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"s\"><mi>s</mi></math> is the length of each side of the square. It's given that the length of each side of a square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 cm\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>. It follows that the area, in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm Superscript 2\"><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 94 right parenthesis squared\"><msup><mfenced><mn>94</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 dot 94\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math>. Therefore, the expression that gives the area, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm Superscript 2\"><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of the square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"94 dot 94\"><mn>94</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>94</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect. This expression gives the perimeter, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"cm\"><mtext>cm</mtext></math>,&nbsp;of the square.</p>","externalid":"d1c64540-1ef9-4449-9ccf-d158b23af654","correct_answer":["D"]}}